                                                                                                                                Content display

                                                                                                                                List item

                                                                                                                                Stable

                                                                                                                                Lists are vertical indexes of text or images arranged horizontally in a row. Lists are often vertically stacked and facilitate efficient scanning.


                                                                                                                                The list item is one of our most-used components, and it makes up more than 80% of Uber’s user interface.


                                                                                                                                With its simple anatomy, the list item element is highly variable to accommodate different use cases.

                                                                                                                                Usage
                                                                                                                                Specs
                                                                                                                                Status & changelog

                                                                                                                                Metrics

                                                                                                                                Cell size & spacing

                                                                                                                                The list item comes in two different sizes, standard and compact. The main difference is the top and bottom padding. Standard list item gives the cell more utility with more artwork and control options. Compact list item allows more content display in limited vertical space.

                                                                                                                                Standard
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                The standard list item has a minimum height of 64 px and the cell height is dynamic when content is taller than 32 px.

                                                                                                                                Compact
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Compact list item has minimum height of 48 and the cell height is always the tallest content with 12 px top and bottom padding.

                                                                                                                                Leading content

                                                                                                                                Artwork smaller than 36 px
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                For artwork sizes, up to 36 px the artwork is centered in a 64 px container. This behavior matches that of the Header component so the navigation icon is always center aligned with list artwork.

                                                                                                                                Artwork larger than 36 px
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                For artwork larger than 36 px the artwork has 16 px padding on both sides. (Note that the padding can be adjusted if there is already proper spacing built into the artwork).

                                                                                                                                Generic letters avatar artwork
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Use the artwork large list item with the 36 px avatar asset, or use the artwork custom list item with 48 px and above the avatar.

                                                                                                                                No artwork
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                If there is no artwork. The text has 16 px padding on both sides.

                                                                                                                                Trailing content

                                                                                                                                Trailing content can be indicators or controls (24 px), badges of any kind, larger elements such as buttons or even more text content.

                                                                                                                                24 px x 24 px icons
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Icons are centered in a 64 px container even for icons in a circle button. This behavior matches that of the Header component so the action icon is always center-aligned with the list icons.

                                                                                                                                Larger controls and indicator
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Wider elements are right aligned with 16 px padding.

                                                                                                                                Trailing text
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Trailing text has 16 px padding on both sides.

                                                                                                                                Type and color

                                                                                                                                List items are widely used for any kind of content. Even though text and icons can be colored differently, we highly recommend the high-contrast primary content and background color.

                                                                                                                                TalkBack

                                                                                                                                In most cases, each list item in a list isn’t considered a button. Rather, TextViews are nested inside of a RecyclerView. Click events are given to the TextViews, which is why they aren’t actually buttons in this case.
